<hr />
<h2>4 · Explain It 🎥</h2>
<p>Take a video on a phone while you show your tree on the wall. Talk through it like you are teaching someone who has never seen it. Try to use these words: <strong>x</strong>, <strong>y</strong>, <strong>coordinate</strong>, <strong>across</strong>, <strong>up</strong>, <strong>home spot</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show your home spot (the red block) and say why you stand on it every time.</li>
<li>Show your finished tree from the front.</li>
<li>Point at one block and read its coordinate out loud: "this one is at x …, y …".</li>
<li>Show one block you placed in the wrong spot at first, and how you fixed it.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write about 4 sentences saying what you will say in your video. You can read from it while filming.</strong></p>
